#: ../../../system/monitor.rst:4
msgid "QEMU Monitor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/monitor.rst:6
msgid ""
"The QEMU monitor is used to give complex commands to the QEMU emulator. You "
"can use it to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/monitor.rst:9
msgid "Remove or insert removable media images (such as CD-ROM or floppies)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/monitor.rst:12
msgid ""
"Freeze/unfreeze the Virtual Machine (VM) and save or restore its state from "
"a disk file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/monitor.rst:15
msgid "Inspect the VM state without an external debugger."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/monitor.rst:18
msgid "Commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/monitor.rst:20
msgid "The following commands are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:19
msgid "``help`` or ``?`` [*cmd*]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:20
msgid "Show the help for all commands or just for command *cmd*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:33
msgid "``clear``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:34
msgid "Clear the monitor screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:46
msgid "``commit``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:47
msgid ""
"Commit changes to the disk images (if -snapshot is used) or backing files. "
"If the backing file is smaller than the snapshot, then the backing file will "
"be resized to be the same size as the snapshot.  If the snapshot is smaller "
"than the backing file, the backing file will not be truncated. If you want "
"the backing file to match the size of the smaller snapshot, you can safely "
"truncate it yourself once the commit operation successfully completes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:66
msgid "``quit`` or ``q``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:67
msgid "Quit the emulator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:80
msgid "``exit_preconfig``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:81
msgid ""
"This command makes QEMU exit the preconfig state and proceed with VM "
"initialization using configuration data provided on the command line and via "
"the QMP monitor during the preconfig state. The command is only available "
"during the preconfig state (i.e. when the --preconfig command line option "
"was in use)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:99
msgid "``block_resize``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:100
msgid ""
"Resize a block image while a guest is running.  Usually requires guest "
"action to see the updated size.  Resize to a lower size is supported, but "
"should be used with extreme caution.  Note that this command only resizes "
"image files, it can not resize block devices like LVM volumes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:116
msgid "``block_stream``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:117
msgid "Copy data from a backing file into a block device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:130
msgid "``block_job_set_speed``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:131
msgid "Set maximum speed for a background block operation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:146
msgid "``block_job_cancel``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:147
msgid "Stop an active background block operation (streaming, mirroring)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:160
msgid "``block_job_complete``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:161
msgid ""
"Manually trigger completion of an active background block operation. For "
"mirroring, this will switch the device to the destination path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:175
msgid "``block_job_pause``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:176
msgid "Pause an active block streaming operation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:189
msgid "``block_job_resume``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:190
msgid "Resume a paused block streaming operation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:202
msgid "``eject [-f]`` *device*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:203
msgid "Eject a removable medium (use -f to force it)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:215
msgid "``drive_del`` *device*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:216
msgid ""
"Remove host block device.  The result is that guest generated IO is no "
"longer submitted against the host device underlying the disk.  Once a drive "
"has been deleted, the QEMU Block layer returns -EIO which results in IO "
"errors in the guest for applications that are reading/writing to the device. "
"These errors are always reported to the guest, regardless of the drive's "
"error actions (drive options rerror, werror)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:233
msgid "``change`` *device* *setting*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:234
msgid "Change the configuration of a device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:236
msgid "``change`` *diskdevice* [-f] *filename* [*format* [*read-only-mode*]]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:237
msgid ""
"Change the medium for a removable disk device to point to *filename*. eg::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:239
msgid "(qemu) change ide1-cd0 /path/to/some.iso"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:241
msgid "``-f``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:242
msgid "forces the operation even if the guest has locked the tray."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:244
msgid "*format* is optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:246
msgid ""
"*read-only-mode* may be used to change the read-only status of the device. "
"It accepts the following values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:249
msgid "retain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:250
msgid "Retains the current status; this is the default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:252
msgid "read-only"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:253
msgid "Makes the device read-only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:255
msgid "read-write"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:256
msgid "Makes the device writable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:258
msgid "``change vnc password`` [*password*]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:260
msgid ""
"Change the password associated with the VNC server. If the new password is "
"not supplied, the monitor will prompt for it to be entered. VNC passwords "
"are only significant up to 8 letters. eg::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:264
msgid ""
"(qemu) change vnc password\n"
"Password: ********"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:282
msgid "``screendump`` *filename*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:283
msgid "Save screen into PPM image *filename*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:296
msgid "``logfile`` *filename*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:297
msgid "Output logs to *filename*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:311
msgid "``trace-event``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:312
msgid "changes status of a trace event"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:325
msgid "``trace-file on|off|flush``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:326
msgid ""
"Open, close, or flush the trace file.  If no argument is given, the status "
"of the trace file is displayed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:340
msgid "``log`` *item1*\\ [,...]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:341
msgid "Activate logging of the specified items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:353
msgid "``savevm`` *tag*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:354
msgid ""
"Create a snapshot of the whole virtual machine. If *tag* is provided, it is "
"used as human readable identifier. If there is already a snapshot with the "
"same tag, it is replaced. More info at :ref:`vm_005fsnapshots`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:359
msgid ""
"Since 4.0, savevm stopped allowing the snapshot id to be set, accepting only "
"*tag* as parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:373
msgid "``loadvm`` *tag*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:374
msgid ""
"Set the whole virtual machine to the snapshot identified by the tag *tag*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:377
msgid "Since 4.0, loadvm stopped accepting snapshot id as parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:390
msgid "``delvm`` *tag*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:391
msgid "Delete the snapshot identified by *tag*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:393
msgid ""
"Since 4.0, delvm stopped deleting snapshots by snapshot id, accepting only "
"*tag* as parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:406
msgid "``one-insn-per-tb [off]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:407
msgid ""
"Run the emulation with one guest instruction per translation block. This "
"slows down emulation a lot, but can be useful in some situations, such as "
"when trying to analyse the logs produced by the ``-d`` option. This only has "
"an effect when using TCG, not with KVM or other accelerators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:412
msgid "If called with option off, the emulation returns to normal mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:424
msgid "``stop`` or ``s``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:425
msgid "Stop emulation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:437
msgid "``cont`` or ``c``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:438
msgid "Resume emulation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:450
msgid "``system_wakeup``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:451
msgid "Wakeup guest from suspend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:463
msgid "``gdbserver`` [*port*]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:464
msgid "Start gdbserver session (default *port*\\=1234)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:476
msgid "``x/``\\ *fmt* *addr*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:477
msgid "Virtual memory dump starting at *addr*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:489
msgid "``xp /``\\ *fmt* *addr*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:490
msgid "Physical memory dump starting at *addr*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:492
msgid ""
"*fmt* is a format which tells the command how to format the data. Its syntax "
"is: ``/{count}{format}{size}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:495
msgid "*count*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:496
msgid "is the number of items to be dumped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:497
msgid "*format*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:498
msgid ""
"can be x (hex), d (signed decimal), u (unsigned decimal), o (octal), c "
"(char) or i (asm instruction)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:500
msgid "*size*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:501
msgid ""
"can be b (8 bits), h (16 bits), w (32 bits) or g (64 bits). On x86, ``h`` or "
"``w`` can be specified with the ``i`` format to respectively select 16 or 32 "
"bit code instruction size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:505
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:507
msgid "Dump 10 instructions at the current instruction pointer::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:509
msgid ""
"(qemu) x/10i $eip\n"
"0x90107063:  ret\n"
"0x90107064:  sti\n"
"0x90107065:  lea    0x0(%esi,1),%esi\n"
"0x90107069:  lea    0x0(%edi,1),%edi\n"
"0x90107070:  ret\n"
"0x90107071:  jmp    0x90107080\n"
"0x90107073:  nop\n"
"0x90107074:  nop\n"
"0x90107075:  nop\n"
"0x90107076:  nop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../hmp-commands.hx:521
msgid "Dump 80 16 bit values at the start of the video memory::"
